result.adr_address: 38 Peel St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Fineprint Coffee

reviews.text:
Great coffee and friendly atmosphere. One of my favorite coffee shops in the area. They also open early (both on weekends and weekdays) which is great. Great pastries and cookies. My daughter loves their energy bites. 

Delicious sourdough bread that you can eat in or take away. Good spot to buy coffee beans to take home as well. 

In the evenings, it is a very nice spot for drinks and bar snacks too.

The cafe has great vibes, bustling with people. I had take away latte which is flavorful. The coffee beans are well toasted. The pastries there looked good, the place seems like a great place for breakfast and tea break.

One of the best coffees you can get on Hong Kong island - rich, velvety and bold piccolo that’s always on point and the perfect pick me up. 

Their baked goods are a hit as well, chocolate chip cookies again one of the best in the city, and they have pretty sick muffins too. If you’re not counting the calories, get a bunch for an emergency stash. 

Great chill vibes, and good attentive service. 

Bonus points for converting into a wine/cocktail bar at night with equally cool vibes. 

Good for: chill weekend coffee, post hike coffee, weekday takeaway, random lazy afternoon
Brilliant flat white, perfect milk texture, delicious flavour. Highly recommend if you're looking for a coffee in the area.
A nice place but very busy. Patrons didn’t seem to mind a cramped space and actually having a coffee outside. Best coffee in HK so far. Food looks good, too. Worth the hill to get here.
